additional_comments: For me, the devil is very much in the detail for AI art. I like detailed pictures, so I've always paid attention to the intricacies of images. The details of AI images frequently just don't make any sense, even if the image overall might look convincing. Human made images have rational details which come from a lived-in understanding of how real things look and function, AI struggles with this because it cannot actually experience or rationalize anything from the outside world.  The problem is most people do not scrutinize images this way, especially if they're scrolling quickly on their phones. I genuinely despise AI imagery and wish it would just go away.
